cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MA, cs.GT

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with maximizing the expected throughput of a wirelessly powered device, which involves information transmission and channel state information. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the optimization of wireless power transfer and data transfer in a network setting. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper involves dynamic programming and optimization of a system with time-varying parameters. 
4. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The paper involves optimization of a system with multiple agents (the access point and the energy harvesting device). 
5. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper involves optimization of a system with multiple agents and a finite horizon, which can be modeled as a game.
